               <msContents>
                  <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <p>
                        
                        ‘The number of acres of lande and meade of <persName>
                           <forename>Thomas</forename> 
                           <surname>Denton</surname>, Esq.</persName>, belonging unto the personage of <placeName key="place_108237">Stratton Audelye in the countye of Oxforde</placeName> whiche landes <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Burlesc</surname>’, Esq., lorde of the sayde manour of <placeName type="manor" role="person" key="place_108238">Stratton</placeName>
                        </persName> hath in exchange of the sayde <persName>
                           <forename>Thomas</forename> 
                           <surname>Denton</surname>
                        </persName> four other landes in the sayde Fealdes and lordeship of <placeName key="place_108237">Stratton</placeName> as hereafter ensueth.’
                        <list>
                            <item>(i) (demesne) 10 a. 1 rood, and a butt.</item>
                            <item>(ii) Now in the tenure of <persName>
                                 <forename>Robert</forename> 
                                 <surname>Macham</surname>
                              </persName>, 3½a.</item>
                            <item>(iii) Now in the tenure of <persName>
                                 <forename>Thomas</forename> 
                                 <surname>King</surname>
                              </persName>, 2a. 1r. 16½ ‘doles’ of meadow.</item>
                            <item>(iv) T.D.’s freehold, late the possession of the monastery of <orgName key="org_109012">Cirencester</orgName> and now in the tenures of <persName>
                                 <forename>William</forename> 
                                 <surname>Jakeman</surname>
                              </persName> and <persName>
                                 <forename>John</forename> 
                                 <surname>Tytmowse</surname>
                              </persName> and <persName>
                                 <forename>Alice</forename> 
                                 <surname>Arnebowrough</surname>
                              </persName>. 1½ a. and 3½ ‘doles’ of meadow in <placeName key="place_108237">Stretton</placeName>.
                                [These lands and the lands for which they were exchanged,
                                are set forth strip by strip against each other, with the situation
                                of each.]</item>
                        </list>
                    </p>
